This is a review of ONE experience I’ve had at Sally Roots, out of several other wonderful experiences. I’m not the type to complain about restaurants, but here we are...We came for brunch the other day and many things went wrong. To begin, the service was truly terrible. While waiting 10 minutes for our server to collect our credit card, we noticed that she was playing on her phone/adjusting the music. (Oy.) I think the restaurant is generally understaffed; we often felt forgotten about. In addition, why is the jerk chicken not offered at 2:30/3pm on a Saturday? We were told that the jerk chicken couldn’t be served until 4pm dinner service resumed, and given that our food didn’t appear til about 3:15, we considered just waiting the 45 minutes for the chicken to become “available.” It’s a shame to write a bad review of a restaurant I like: I had hoped it would become a regular spot for me, but lately the experience has been less than ideal. Though I will probably will return for dinner, I don’t think I’ll be back for brunch.

My husband and I have been to Sally Roots a couple of times now and really like it.  The design of the restaurant evokes the Caribbean - pastel colors and sunny lighting.  The bar is particularly pretty.  The staff are easy going and friendly.  Johnny, who I believe is an owner, is a welcoming bartender.  All of the cocktails are great and reasonably priced.  Try the frozens. I've had the veggie curry bowl, which is a little spicy and pretty rich.  My husband has had the goat curry, which he really enjoyed - tender with a chili-forward curry.  It's a great addition to Bushwick; we'll definitely be back.
Love this place. Fun never stops. Food delicious.  Beautiful people... and the drinks  uff. Super. Good price. Mucho rum.
I've tried a lot of their dishes; all 5 out of 5 fire flame emoji rankings. All meals under $20; great cocktails and drink selection. Staff is fun and friendly. Ask for James the bartender he's lit.
The sign said good vibes inside and that's all you need to know. The Miami Vice (off the menu frozen drink) was amazing, and the staff is the coolest. ✌️
The food is good. Great service ambition excellent

The bar and ambience were really nice. Cocktails were strong and tasty. The jerk chicken was flavorful but needed more sauce. The salmon was ok. I'll definitely be back as it's a good addition to the neighborhood.

I'm from out of town visiting and stopped into Sally Roots last night. Didn't even want to be out late but the bar tender ended up being an amazing human being so we stayed until the end of the night. That guy knows what great customer service is!
Great atmosphere and food. The island avocado and short rib are both incredible.
Didnt try the food but the drinks were amazing. Really great cocktails for a good price and nice non alcoholic options too. Also, the people that work here are super nice!!

Nice beer selection at a decent price. Had the food and it was a mixed bag. Brussels sprouts with pork belly was amazing but the two bowl dishes we had were below expectation. One with oxtail was more fat than meat while the curry chicken one was more like chicken soup. It's got a nice setup and the backyard is beautiful. Would definitely come back here for drinks (and the Brussels Sprouts) but probably not to eat. Perhaps the mains are better.

Me & my friends went here the other night to check it out as we heard a new place opened up and we really liked it. Very nice creative cocktails, strong & delicious. Food was tasty. Well drinks are cheap. Superb staff. Good music. Huge back garden. Nice toilets lol. The indoor isn't huge though so I imagine it'll get rammed when people realise how awesome it is. I recommend!
